GoodKook's VLSI Tutorial using OpenSource Tools
e-mail: goodkook@gmail.com

Requirement Tools:

    1. Magic VLSI Layout:
        https://github.com/RTimothyEdwards/magic.git

    2. Netgen: LVS
        https://github.com/RTimothyEdwards/netgen.git
        
    3. Ngspice: ngspice-41 (latest version, as of 2023, Oct.)
        Homepage: https://ngspice.sourceforge.io/
                    https://sourceforge.net/projects/ngspice/files/ng-spice-rework/41/

        Download:
            Manual: https://sourceforge.net/projects/ngspice/files/ng-spice-rework/41/ngspice-41-manual.pdf/download
            Source: https://sourceforge.net/projects/ngspice/files/ng-spice-rework/41/ngspice-41.tar.gz/download

        Install:
            $ tar xvf ngspice-41.tar.gz
            $ cd ngspice-41
            $ ./configure
            $ make
            $ sudo make install

    4. xschem
        homepage: https://github.com/StefanSchippers/xschem
        Manual: http://repo.hu/projects/xschem/xschem_man/xschem_man.html

        Download & Install:
            $ git clone https://github.com/StefanSchippers/xschem.git
            $ cd xschem
            $ ./configure
            $ make
            $ sudo make install

    4-1. xschem-gaw: waveform viewer
        https://github.com/StefanSchippers/xschem-gaw
        
        Download & Install:
            $ git clonw https://github.com/StefanSchippers/xschem-gaw.git

    5. PDKs
	5-1. 0.5um PDK from AMIc5 / ETRI

    5-2. Open source PDK(OPTIONAL): Google's skywater 130
		homepage: http://opencircuitdesign.com/open_pdks/index.html

		Download & Install:

			$ git clone git://opencircuitdesign.com/open_pdks

			or

			tar-ball, http://opencircuitdesign.com/open_pdks/archive/open_pdks-1.0.450.tgz

			$ cd open_psks
			$ ./configure --enable-sky130-pdk --enable-sram-sky130
			$ make
			$ sudo make install
			$ make veryclean


